The paper discusses the Medium Access Control protocol of Power Line Communication networks, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the analytical model and computational complexity, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the effect of specific Homeplug/IEEE 1901 features on the magnitude of misprediction errors, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the priority resolution scheme defined in Homeplug/IEEE 1901, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the traffic differentiation provided by the different contention parameters, which falls under the category of performance (cs.PF).
